      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Lieberman Asset</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter from Charles W Pluckhahn says Sen Joseph I Lieberman's record of favoring businesses and also consumers is no paradox; says issue is not whether to regulate but how to do so in way that benefits businesses and consumers (Aug 27 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>It's a strength, not a weakness, that Joseph I. Lieberman has found a way to be pro-business while also requiring companies to pay attention to human needs (''As a Senator, Lieberman Is Proudly Pro-Business,'' front page, Aug. 27).</p>
        <p>Smart regulations benefit consumers as well as businesses. Food and drug regulations give confidence in what people are buying. Automobile-safety regulations reduce health care costs. The clearest example is the privacy issue that keeps many consumers off the Internet. Smarter companies are asking the government to establish rules.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>It's a strength, not a weakness, that Joseph I. Lieberman has found a way to be pro-business while also requiring companies to pay attention to human needs (''As a Senator, Lieberman Is Proudly Pro-Business,'' front page, Aug. 27).</p>
        <p>Smart regulations benefit consumers as well as businesses. Food and drug regulations give confidence in what people are buying. Automobile-safety regulations reduce health care costs. The clearest example is the privacy issue that keeps many consumers off the Internet. Smarter companies are asking the government to establish rules.</p>
        <p>The issue is not whether to regulate but how to do so in a way that benefits businesses and consumers. Life is full of paradoxes, but Senator Lieberman's record of favoring businesses and consumers isn't one of them.</p>
        <p>CHARLES W. PLUCKHAHN  Newton, Mass., Aug. 27, 2000</p>
      </block>
